diff:1670647132:1670015799:=51,65c51%0a%3c #foxbegin 221210-043853-209890#%0a%3c (:div1 class=expansionhead:)%0a%3c !!!Culture and language %0a%3c -> - nathandeyak%0a%3c -> [-09.12.2022 - 20:38-]%0a%3c >>rfloat%3c%3c   %0a%3c (:if1 authgroup @tas:)%0a%3c {[foxdelrange button 221210-043853-209890 {$FullName} ]}%0a%3c (:if1end:)%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c (:div1end:) %0a%3c >>messageitem%3c%3c %0a%3c This is a very illustrative scene that pokes at the deep intertwining of language with culture, and culture with language. The changes in speech that he is trying to make are largely not phonological, but rather concern the manner and norms of his speech, which are hard to pin down as strictly linguistic or strictly cultural. Even emotion and pitch are racially and dialectically coded, and thus present a roadblock for the new worker to succeed in his job.%0a%3c >>%3c%3c%0a%3c #foxend 221210-043853-209890#%0a---%0a> %0a
